        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-11-13T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-11-13T02:00:00-05:00" n="283" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d283">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01/11–1347: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Mukden</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ward</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mukden</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-11-13T15:00:00+08:00">November 13, 1947—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 13—12:31 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>346. General Lo Cho-ying, formerly Governor [of] Kwangtung, arrived Mukden
                    November 11 as Vice Director President’s NE Headquarters, altho some sources
                    state he has been appointed as Director. Persistent rumors Chen Cheng, who has
                    been ill with stomach ulcers, will be relieved and replaced by Lo. Chen may
                    remain as titular head for time, but many observers believe actual replacement
                    will be made as soon as possible without causing loss face by Chen.</p>
                <p>Sent Embassy, repeated Department as 346 and Changchun.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ward</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
